<item>
            <title>[AMQ-7327] HTTP transport connector doesn&apos;t limit the message size using maxFrameSize</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-7327</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;ws&lt;/tt&gt; transport connector uses the &lt;tt&gt;maxFrameSize&lt;/tt&gt; to set binary and text message size limit.&lt;br/&gt;
However the &lt;tt&gt;http&lt;/tt&gt; transport connector doesn&apos;t and the user needs a hack on &lt;tt&gt;jetty.xml&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
The &lt;tt&gt;http&lt;/tt&gt; transport connector should directly use the &lt;tt&gt;maxFrameSize&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
